cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on motion planning for automated vehicles in uncertain and occluded environments. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper mentions impaired perception due to adverse weather conditions and occlusions, which can be addressed through computer vision techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of optimization-based motion planning, which is a common AI technique. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is possible as the paper may involve learning-based approaches for handling uncertainty and occlusions. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also possible as the paper deals with control of automated vehicles in uncertain environments.
